summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of seven concrete suppliers (A through G) operating in West Yorkshire, UK, detailing their market penetration and average purchase frequency. Supplier A demonstrates the highest market penetration at 46%, alongside the highest average number of purchases in the last three months at 2.96. As market penetration decreases among suppliers B through G, the average number of purchases also generally declines. Suppliers B, C, and D show moderate market penetration (36% to 31%) with average purchases ranging from 1.54 to 1.27. Suppliers E and F exhibit identical figures, with 26% market penetration and 1.03 average purchases. Supplier G has the lowest market penetration at 16% and the lowest average number of purchases at 0.83. The structure highlights a correlation between market penetration and customer purchase frequency across these regional concrete suppliers.
